	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_71937"><p>I don't mean to be a troll or anything like that and I haven't really looked at the how the Perl 6 syntax has evolved over the years.</p><p>So, out of curiosity I decided to take a look at the commit and I was bewildered by code such as:</p><p><span class="substr"> </span> <code> <br>%*pads{$*current-block} = {};<br>for $ -&gt; $statement {<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp; self.find-vars($statement, 'statement');<br>}<br> </code> </p><p>I mean, I can see the point in Perl 5 sigils. They're not pretty, but they're acceptable and they didn't bother me in these almost 10 years I've been programming in Perl.</p><p>But</p></div>
		
	
	</div>
