		<div id="comment_body_72028"><blockquote><div><p> <em>Firstly, minimising the number of operators, especially in perl 6's case, would be positive.</em><span class="substr"> </span> </p></div></blockquote><p>Why?</p><p>No, seriously.  Why?</p><p>It's obvious you have a target number in mind.  Quantify it.  If there are facts, discoverable facts, for the design of an ideal programming language, let's be engineers about it.  Be specific.  "Too many" is not specific.  "Fewer" is not helpful.  "I know it when I see it" is opinion, not science.  Be bold; back up your assertions.</p><p>I cheerfully ignore the reductio ad lambda calculus argument</p></div>
		
	
	</div>
	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_72028"></div>

</div>


